From: PanicOS <noreply@panicos>
Date: 2026-05-15
Subject: [PATCH] sound: soc: sunxi_v2: configure HDMI routing for AHUB

The Armbian sunxi_v2 AHUB driver (imported via 0224-0701) writes the
per-TDM tx_route correctly but never programs the registers that
actually connect the AHUB output to the HDMI controller's audio input
on Allwinner H616/H700.

The original Allwinner BSP (orangepi-xunlong/linux-orangepi
orange-pi-4.9-sun50iw9) does three additional things when the TDM in
use is the HDMI one (tdm_num == 1 == SUNXI_AHUB_HDMI_ID):

  1. Enable ALL 4 SDO output lanes (SDO0..SDO3) on that TDM, not just
     the single SDO selected by tx_pin. The HDMI audio block samples
     multiple lanes for layout / HBR support.
  2. Write 1 << HDMI_SRC_SEL (= 0x10) to SUNXI_AHUB_CTL so the HDMI
     clock is sourced from the AHUB rather than from an external pin.
  3. Write 0x10 to I2S_OUT_CHMAP0(tdm, 0) — the BSP-specific channel
     slot map used for HDMI audio.

Without these, the AHUB happily transmits valid I2S on TDM1 SDO0 but
none of it reaches the dw-hdmi audio block.

Sources (BSP):
  sound/soc/sunxi/sunxi_ahub.c:557   (HDMI_SRC_SEL)
  sound/soc/sunxi/sunxi_ahub_daudio.c:76-90 (SDO0..3 enable for HDMI)
  sound/soc/sunxi/sunxi_ahub_daudio.c:485-489 (CH0MAP0 = 0x10)

Signed-off-by: PanicOS

--- a/sound/soc/sunxi_v2/snd_sunxi_ahub.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sunxi_v2/snd_sunxi_ahub.c
@@ -640,6 +640,8 @@ static void sunxi_ahub_dai_tx_route(struct sunxi_ahub_info *ahub_info,
 {
        struct regmap *regmap = NULL;
        unsigned int tdm_num, tx_pin;
+       /* SUNXI_AHUB_HDMI_ID: TDM index internally wired to dw-hdmi audio. */
+       const unsigned int SUNXI_AHUB_HDMI_ID = 1;
        unsigned int apb_num;

        SND_LOG_DEBUG(HLOG, "%s\n", enable ? "on" : "off");
@@ -668,6 +670,28 @@ tx_route_enable:
        /* enable tx drq */
        regmap_update_bits(regmap, SUNXI_AHUB_APBIF_TX_IRQ_CTL(apb_num),
                           0x1 << APBIF_TX_DRQ, 0x1 << APBIF_TX_DRQ);
+
+       /*
+        * BSP-style HDMI hub setup. Allwinner H616/H700 internally wires the
+        * AHUB's TDM #1 to the dw-hdmi audio input block, but the connection
+        * is only enabled when:
+        *  (a) all 4 SDO lanes are enabled (not just tx_pin), AND
+        *  (b) SUNXI_AHUB_CTL bit HDMI_SRC_SEL selects AHUB as HDMI clk source.
+        * The vendor BSP also writes CH0MAP0 = 0x10 (channel-slot mapping
+        * for HDMI). Verified live on RG35XX Pro 2026-05-15: audio data does
+        * not reach the dw-hdmi block without these three writes.
+        */
+       if (tdm_num == SUNXI_AHUB_HDMI_ID) {
+               regmap_update_bits(regmap, SUNXI_AHUB_I2S_CTL(tdm_num),
+                                  0xF << I2S_CTL_SDO0_EN,
+                                  0xF << I2S_CTL_SDO0_EN);
+               regmap_update_bits(regmap, SUNXI_AHUB_CTL,
+                                  0x1 << HDMI_SRC_SEL,
+                                  0x1 << HDMI_SRC_SEL);
+               regmap_write(regmap,
+                            SUNXI_AHUB_I2S_OUT_CHMAP0(tdm_num, 0),
+                            0x10);
+       }
        return;

 tx_route_disable:
